Go to Settings → Bluetooth & Devices → Printers & Scanners
• Or Settings → Devices (for some versions of Windows 11)
• Here you can view, add, or remove devices connected to your PC

Add a printer  
1. Open Settings → Printers & Scanners → Add Device
2. Windows will automatically search for printers connected via USB or network
3. If the printer is detected, click Add Device
4. For Wi-Fi or network printers, make sure they're connected to the same network as your PC
5. If the printer is not found, you can manually add it via "The printer I want is not listed"


